The Government of Kenya has said all schools will remain closed until January 2021 due to rising cases of COVID-19 in the country. Final year exams, usually written in October and November, have also been cancelled. George Magoha, Kenya's Education Minister, said students would repeat a year as schools had closed in mid-March, three months after the school calendar had begun, the BBC reports.Â 


Daily Active "The 2020 school calendar year will be considered lost due to COVID-19 restrictions," he said. The decision would apply to public and private schools. Kenya has more than 8,000 confirmed cases of Coronavirus with at least 164 deaths. President Uhuru Kenyatta on Monday announced a phased reopening of the country, including the lifting of travel restrictions in the main cities of Nairobi and Mombasa.